{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cf2320e1-b683-4c65-b1d6-2de66a034e0d","content":"Use MAUI's `#if` platform directives combined with the standard `IServiceCollection` registration in `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n#if ANDROID\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Android.AndroidNotificationService>();\n#elif IOS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.iOS.IosNotificationService>();\n#elif WINDOWS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Windows.WindowsNotificationService>();\n#endif\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Place each implementation under its `Platforms/<OS>/` folder so it only compiles for that target.\n- The preprocessor symbols (`ANDROID`, `IOS`, `WINDOWS`) are defined automatically by the MAUI SDK — no manual setup needed.\n- Inject `INotificationService` via constructor injection anywhere; the right implementation resolves at runtime.\n- This won't break on any platform because each `#if` branch only references types that exist for that compilation target.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"931a6f19-4baf-4096-9065-3cdc0e085c4b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI dependency injection — specifically how to register platform-specific implementations of an `INotificationService` interface in `MauiProgram.cs`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase-specific task.","outputTokens":372,"requestId":"1019:7B46E:14FA056:17A54CB:69FD365F"},"id":"e2ed72c1-8812-4f25-a34b-b88bb9ec3567","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:03:35.260Z","parentId":"673d9c86-d5f4-446a-800d-a1d6ffef121f"}
